About
----------------------------------------

These scripts are used to generate SRPMS of the TOMOYO Linux kernel, based on
the associated upstream kernel package. For each package, the official SRPM is
downloaded and the SPEC file is modified using a patch.



Dependencies
----------------------------------------

  patch
  rpmdevtools
  rpm-build



Installation
----------------------------------------

Put the scripts into a folder and specify the folder in $HOME/.bashrc:

  export CCS_SCRIPT_DIR="$HOME/buildscripts"

All sources are downloaded and kept in the $CCS_SOURCE_DIR folder:

  export CCS_SOURCE_DIR="$HOME/sources"

The following variable should also be exported:

  export CCS_BUILD_DIR="$HOME/rpmbuild"



Usage
----------------------------------------

To build the kernel RPM package for Enterprise Linux 6:

  ./build-el6.sh

To build the kernel RPM package for Fedora 16:

  ./build-f16.sh

To build the userspace tools RPM package for Enterprise Linux 6:

  ./build-tools-el6.sh

To build the userspace tools RPM package for Fedora 16:

  ./build-tools-f16.sh



